cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach for single-image super-resolution. The use of deep learning to generate kriging weights also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The statistical nature of the proposed method may also make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of end-to-end learning suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
